This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as single-image super-resolution and surface normal estimation, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel approach to training CNNs to maintain natural image statistics, which involves looking at the distribution of features in an image and training the network to generate images with natural feature distributions. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories, as it involves training a neural network. Additionally, the paper mentions that their approach reduces the number of images required for training, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions high-resolution surface normal estimation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
